    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1266</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Statements in your despatch June 11, No. 533, are of interest.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d656fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_448">p. 448</ref>.</note>
                    Department would like to receive earliest possible moment all available and
                    authentic data in keeping with your observation in the third paragraph of first
                    page of your note to Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_OJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Osborne</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
